      <p>
        My CI/CD solution, replacing building images and deploying services entirely within GitHub Actions runners.
      </p>
      Instead, I just call an endpoint hosted within my homelab cluster that:
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li>Pulls the latest code from the configured GitHub repository</li>
        <li>
          Kicks off a build process using Docker's
          <span class="bg-violet-800/25 font-mono rounded-sm border border-violet-800 px-1 py-0.5 text-sm">
            buildx
          </span>
          Kubernetes driver
        </li>
        <li>Restarts the specified Kubernetes services after builds are finished</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        The only thing that needs to run in a GitHub Action for any configured project is
        <span class="bg-violet-800/25 font-mono rounded-sm border border-violet-800 px-1 py-0.5 text-sm">
          curl
        </span>
        pointed at the corresponding Build Hook endpoint <i>(with a valid bearer token)</i>.
      </p>

      <p>
